      "span_text": "Traditional candidate gene studies have often produced contradictory findings, while genome-wide association studies (GWAS) have only explained a fraction of the heritability of such disorders.  This review will focus on psychiatric genetic research into schizophrenia, OCD and bipolar disorder in South African populations with reference to global research, as the vast majority of South African research to date has been performed on these disorders.",
